definition.value: A secondary alkyl sulfate oxoanion where the substiuents are arranged so the sulfate is in (R)-configuration. Published in DOI:10.1002/adsc.201100864
A secondary alcohol where the substiuents are arranged so the hydroxy group is in (S)-configuration. Published in DOI:10.1002/adsc.201100864

A quinolone that is 4,6,7,8-tetrahydroquinolin-5(1H)-one substituted by methyl, (2-methoxyethoxy)carbonyl, 2-fluorophenyl and 4-chlorophenyl groups at positions 2, 3, 4 and 7, respectively (the 4S,7S-stereoisomer). It is an inhibitor of voltage-dependent anion channel 3 (VDAC3) and a ferroptosis inducer.

A fluorene that is N-9H-fluoren-9-ylidenehydroxylamine substituted by N-cyclohexylsulfonyl groups at positions 2 and 7. It induces ferroptosis via degradation of GPX4 and also binds and activates squalene synthase.
A  chlorophenol that is phenol substituted by 5 chloro groups.

An oxaspiro compound that is 1,2-dioxaspiro[4.5]decane substituted by methyl, 2-hydroxyethyl and tert-butyl groups at positions 3, 3 and 8, respectivey (the 5s,8s-stereoisomer). It induces ferroptosis in cancer cells by indirectly inhibiting glutathione peroxidase 4 (GPX4) enzymatic function and directly oxidizes iron leading to widespread lipid peroxidation.
A disaccharide derivative that is the 6-aminohexyl glycoside of the disaccharide alpha-L-fucopyranosyl-(1->2)-alpha-L-fucopyranose.

A thiazolidinone that is 2-sulfanylidene-1,3-thiazolidin-4-one substituted by 3-{[3-(morpholin-4-yl)propyl]amino}-3-oxopropyl and 4-ethylbenzylidene groups at positions 3 and 5, respectively. It is a ferroptosis inducer.

A linear tetrasaccharide derivative that is the 6-aminohexyl glycoside of the tetrasaccharide alpha-L-fucopyranosyl-(1->2)-alpha-L-fucopyranosyl-(1->2)-alpha-L-fucopyranosyl-(1->2)-alpha-L-fucopyranose.
Tetraanion of a lipid IVA with unspecified (3R)-3-hydroxyacyl chains.

A member of the class of furans that is furan substituted by propyl, carboxy and hydroxymethyl groups at positions 2, 3 and 4, respectively. It is an inducer of antibiotic biosynthesis in Streptomyces species.
Kdo-lipid IVA deprotonated at both phosphono groups and at the uronic acid carboxy group and with unspecified (3R)-3-hydroxyacyl chains.
(Kdo)2-lipid IVA deprotonated at both phosphono groups and at the uronic acid carboxy group and with unspecified (3R)-3-hydroxyacyl chains.
(Kdo)2-(acyl)-lipid IVA deprotonated at both phosphono groups and at the uronic acid carboxy group and with unspecified (3R)-3-hydroxyacyl chains.
A lipid A oxoanion obtained via deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphate OH groups of an alpha-Kdo-(2->4)-alpha-Kdo-(2->6)-lipid A with unspecified (3R)-3-hydroxyacyl chains.
An N-acyl-gamma-aminobutyric acid resulting from the monoacetylation of the nitrogen of GABA.
A glutamic acid derivative that is glutamic acid substituted by a methyl group at position 4.
